^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Well done Babs. If Babs keeps this up, we will have to find a student more interesting for the kibs -:). We already discussed the bidding. A couple of points on the play and defense. Babs did well to ruff her 3rd spade before drawing trumps. In general you should draw trumps ASAP. You never have to delay drawing trumps when ruffing in the long hand. But the most common reason to delay drawing trumps, as on this hand, is when you need to ruff something in the hand with short trumps. |
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|And if you draw trumps you won't be able to ruff. That situation most commonly occurs in a 5-3 fit, where you need 3 rounds to draw trump, so if you need to ruff in the hand with 3 trumps you have to do so before drawing 3 rounds of trump (which you need to do with an 8 card fit since they are at best 4-2).|
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
