^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|It is not clear whether or not West should double. Whenever they buy the hand and you have a singleton or void in partner's suit, that makes it more likely that you will defeat the hand. You could easily be getting a ruff, and, since you are short, it is more likely both opponents have 2 or even 3 cards in partner's suit and partner will be able to cash some tricks. |
