NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So the singleton heart favors doubling. East also has a club trick. So, it is very possible that 5@D is down 1 off the top, losing a heart, a heart ruff and the @CA. And the spade honors might produce a trick, depending on who has the @SA and @SQ. So double is not unreasonable, but it is certainly possible that 5@D will make.|
